# Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## Admin Dashboard — Assam Association Delhi

---

# 1. Overview

## 1.1 Purpose

The Admin Dashboard is a secure, user-friendly content management system (CMS) designed for non-technical users to manage website content, bookings, documents, and media efficiently.

## 1.2 Goals

* Enable easy content updates without technical knowledge
* Provide centralized control over all website data
* Ensure scalability, security, and performance
* Maintain clean UX for low learning curve

---

# 2. Users & Roles

## 2.1 User Type

* Admin (1–2 users only)

## 2.2 Permissions

* Full CRUD access across all modules
* Authentication required for all actions

---

# 3. Core Modules

## 3.1 Dashboard Overview

### Features

* Summary cards:

  * Total bookings
  * Pending bookings
  * Total notices
  * Total documents
* Recent activity list

---

## 3.2 Booking Management

### Features

* View all bookings (table view)
* Filters:

  * Status (Pending, Approved, Rejected)
  * Date
  * Facility

### Actions

* Approve booking
* Reject booking
* View details

### Logic

* On approval:

  * Update status
  * Add entry to blocked_dates
  * Trigger confirmation email

### Export

* Export bookings as CSV/Excel

---

## 3.3 Notices Management

### Features

* Create, edit, delete notices
* Rich text editor
* Optional PDF upload
* Pin important notice

### Fields

* Title
* Content
* PDF (optional)
* Pinned toggle

---

## 3.4 Documents Management

### Features

* Upload documents
* Categorize by:

  * Category
  * Year

### Actions

* Upload
* Delete
* Edit metadata

---

## 3.5 Gallery Management

### Features

* Create album
* Upload multiple images
* Set cover image
* Add YouTube video links

### Actions

* Delete media
* Edit album

---

## 3.6 Committee Management

### Features

* Add/edit/remove members

### Fields

* Name
* Role
* Image

---

## 3.7 Services Management

### Features

* Manage facilities content

### Fields

* Name
* Description
* Image

---

## 3.8 Contact Messages

### Features

* View messages submitted via contact form
* No reply system required

---

# 4. UI/UX Requirements

## 4.1 Design Principles

* Clean, minimal dashboard UI
* Large clickable areas
* Clear labels
* No technical jargon

## 4.2 Components

* Sidebar navigation
* Top header with user info
* Data tables
* Forms with validation

## 4.3 Feedback System

* Toast notifications for:

  * Success
  * Error
  * Warning

---

# 5. Validation & Error Handling

## 5.1 Frontend Validation

* Required fields validation
* Proper input formats

## 5.2 Backend Validation

* Schema validation (Zod or equivalent)
* Sanitization of inputs

## 5.3 Error Handling

* Standard error response format:

```
{
  success: false,
  message: "Error message",
  errorCode: "OPTIONAL_CODE"
}
```

## 5.4 Success Response

```
{
  success: true,
  data: {}
}
```

---

# 6. Authentication & Security

## 6.1 Authentication

* Firebase Authentication
* Email/password login

## 6.2 Authorization

* Admin-only access

## 6.3 Security Practices

* Protected routes
* Firestore rules (admin write only)
* Input validation
* Rate limiting (API level)

---

# 7. Performance Requirements

* Lazy loading for tables
* Pagination for large datasets
* Image compression via Cloudinary

---

